{"word":"σεβαστός","slug":"σεβαστός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>σεβαστός, ή, όν</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:σεβάζομαι\">σεβάζομαι</a></el>] ‘meriting exceptional respect’, <b>revered, august</b> as translation of <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> augustus in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ref.\">ref.</a> to the Roman emperor, <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a> Σεβαστός</el> His Imperial Majesty <b><a href='B:510 25:21'>Ac 25:21</a>, <a href='B:510 25:25'>25</a>.</b> As honorary attribution <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:σπεῖρα\">σπεῖρα</a> Σεβαστή</el> Imperial cohort <b><a href='B:510 27:1'>Ac 27:1</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:σέβασμα\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:σέβω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}